name: skyfish
description:
Skyfish (also known as Rods or Solar Entities) is a term used in cryptozoology, ufology, and outdoor photography to refer to elongated artifacts in the form of light-rods produced by cameras. They are typically seen in pictures taken during the half of the day when the sun is out.

This image was composed for the #HENOSY event, celebrating half a year of HEN's existence.

1080 x 1080 px, 300 dpi .png file
